    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted under risk-informed rationale: model influence is Medium, the single test condition is the regulatory standard condition, and all three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance criteria with substantial margin. The mesh convergence study confirmed discretization error is well-controlled. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the 510(k) submission claim.",
